Business Brief -- Vulcan International Corp.:
   Sale of Treasury Shares
   Is Authorized by Directors
In American Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday,
Vulcan common closed at $18, unchanged.
   The Cincinnati company said proceeds will be used to
reduce existing bank debt, among other purposes. Vulcan said
it does not intend to issue any transferable rights to buy
its treasury shares.
   Vulcan International makes shoe lasts, heels, soles, and
other rubber and plastic products and bowling pins.